<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG-20191130-WA0003-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&amp;ssl=1" alt="Govt. should enforce ban on religious activities in stadia ― Rojenny Proprietor" class="amp-wp-295b586"> Rommy Ezeonwuka, Proprietor of Rojenny Stadium and Tourists Village, has called on government at all levels to ban religious and other non-sporting activities in all spots sports stadia in the country. Ezeonwuka made the call when he received members of Sports Writers Association of Nigeria (SWAN), Anambra chapter, who were on tour of sports facilities in the state. The tour of sports was part of the three day SWAN Week activities in the state. Continue reading Govt. should enforce ban on religious activities in stadia ― Rojenny Proprietor at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard